      "description": "Requires cigarettes and tobacco products to be stored for sale behind a counter. Requires advertisements that promote or encourage the purchase or use of cigarettes or tobacco products to be placed at least ten feet away from children's products, toys, cookies, candy, ice cream, gum, or snacks if the establishment is less than one thousand square feet. For establishments one thousand square feet or larger, advertisements that promote or encourage the purchase or use of cigarettes or tobacco products must be at least twenty-five feet away. Requires advertisements that promote or encourage the purchase or use of cigarettes or tobacco products to be placed at least four feet from the floor. Permits exceptions for retail tobacco stores, bars, or establishments where the minimum age for admission is eighteen. (SD1)"
